<h1>Problem 1327 - 2011 IMO, P5 of 6, N</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Let \(f\) be a function from the set of integers to the set of positive integers. Suppose that, for any two integers \(m\) and \(n\), the difference \(f(m) - f(n)\) is divisible by \(f(m- n)\). Prove that, for all integers \(m\) and \(n\) with \(f(m) \leq f(n)\), the number \(f(n)\) is divisible by \(f(m)\).</p>
